Preheat oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7. Place the @goat's cheese{100%g} on a lined #baking tray{}.

In a #small bowl{}, mix the @Italian herbs{1%sachet} with a good glug of @oil{to taste}. Pour the herby oil over the goat's cheese and bake in the oven until starting to melt, ~{5-6%minutes}.

Meanwhile, chop the @tomato{2}(chopped into 2cm chunks).

Trim the @salad leaves{120%g}, quarter lengthways and roughly chop widthways.

Toss the salad leaves and tomato with a drizzle of @oil{to taste} and the @balsamic vinegar{1%sachet}. Season to taste with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}.

Divide your dressed salad between #bowls{}. Top with the warmed goat's cheese.

Tear over small pieces of @smoked salmon{100%g} to finish.